==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skive
<hw>Skive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>sk⟦imac⟧fa</ets> a shaving, slice, E. <ets>shive</ets>,
<ets>sheave</ets>.]</ety> <def>The iron lap used by diamond polishers in
finishing the facets of the gem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skive
<hw>Skive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To pare or shave off
the rough or thick parts of (hides or leather).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skiver</ent>⟦br⟧
